# COLLADA meshes are verbose XML text. Store them gzip-compressed in git
# (clean filter) and transparently decompress on checkout (smudge filter).
# ~10x smaller blobs, byte-identical working-tree files, no LFS needed.
#
# REQUIRED one-time per clone (git won't auto-run filters from .gitattributes):
#   ./scripts/setup-git-filters.sh
# Without it, checkout of *.dae will FAIL loudly (filter is marked required).
*.dae filter=daegz -text
